rComments: Very approachable and generous with grading.  Course was a little dull but he sightread a Debussy Prelude better than I could ever play it...

FANTASTIC! He's going on Sabbatical next year, which makes me so sad. I really wanted to take another course with him.  He also memorized everyone's names by the second class.  That's over 20, if not 30, students' names two days after the first class.  He's incredible.
Fantastic teacher. Extremely intelligent and open. Not single minded and stubborn like some of the other theory teachers. Very kind and helpful.

One of the best two theory profs I have EVER had. He really wants everyone to do well and understand the concepts behind the pieces that he teaches and he is very approachable for extra help outside of class. Not only that, but this guy is SO talented. He sightreads like no other.
WONDERFUL!! He was nerdy but in an endearing way, very clear lessons with helpful handouts, fair assignments, and totally approachable for extra help outside of class. One of the best profs I've had.
